<HEADLINE>
TAIWAN TO HOST INTERNATIONAL BALLET GALA IN JULY
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Jan.  9 (CNA) 01/09/07  19:46:16 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
An international ballet gala scheduled for July 25 in Taipei will
bring 12 ballet stars from various countries who will present a
mixture of classical and contemporary ballet pieces, the chief
organizer of the event said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Wang Tzer-shing, a former ballerina of the Los Angeles Classical
Ballet and prime mover behind the gala, told reporters that she
selected the performers based on their professional achievements.
</P>
<P>
Wang was a ballet instructor at the Long Beach Ballet Academy
before she moved to Taiwan in 2000 to continue to teach classical
ballet.
</P>
<P>
According to her, the classical features at the gala will include
such well- known pieces as Swan Lake, Sleeping Beauty, Le
Corsaire, Romeo and Juliet, La Bayadere, Don Quixote and Grand
Pas Classique.
</P>
<P>
The stars will come from renowned ballet troupes, including ABT,
Kirov Ballet, Paris Opera, Stuttgart Ballet and Berlin State
Ballet. Audiences in Taiwan will have an opportunity to
appreciate their exemplary performances, as well as their unique
artisty and personal charm first-hand, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
The gala will take place at the Taipei International Convention
Center's Plenary Hall.
</P>
<P>
An event of such magnitude is also expected to draw ballet
enthusiasts from other countries to watch the rare performances,
she added.
</P>
<P>
According to Wang, Dance Europe magazine has already published a
report on the gala, and its editor, Emma Manning, has indicated
that she will come to Taipei to see the performance and write a
review.
</P>
<P>
The 12 ballet stars are: Nowenn Daniel, Marcelo Gomers, Paloma
Herrera, Mikhail Kaniskin, Ilja Louwen, Leo Mujic, Olesia
Novikova, Karl Paquette, Iana Salenko, Leonid Sarafanov, Elena
Tentschikowa and Marian Walter.
</P>
